/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/num_p5_25_124/rounds/round_1/merge_stdout.log:1:{"findings":[{"id":"F-002","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Permit-based bridge entrypoints let arbitrary callers redirect a signer’s funds to attacker-chosen recipients, chains, and routes","locations":["onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:257","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:269","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:272","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:275","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:286","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:288","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:382","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:395","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:398","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:407","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:412","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:424","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:427","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:476","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:489","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:492","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:501","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:506","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:518","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:521"],"claim":"The `*WithPermit` and `*WithTransferPermit` bridge entrypoints use the signature only to authorize token movement into the router/token vault, but they never require `msg.sender == from` and do not authenticate bridge-critical fields such as destination recipient, destination chain, or swap path. A third party who obtains a valid permit-style signature can therefore submit the transaction themselves and choose where the bridged value ultimately goes.","impact":"A malicious frontend, relayer, or signature collector can steal a victim’s funds by consuming the victim’s permit and bridging the value to an attacker-controlled address or chain. In the swap variants, the attacker can also choose the output route and asset, converting the victim’s funds into attacker-preferred destination assets.","paths":["Victim signs a permit for `anySwapOutUnderlyingWithPermit`; attacker submits the call first with `to` set to the attacker and `toChainID` set to the attacker’s preferred chain.","Victim signs for a cross-chain swap permit; attacker calls `anySwapOutExactTokensForTokensUnderlyingWithPermit` or `anySwapOutExactTokensForNativeUnderlyingWithPermit` with attacker-chosen `path` and `to`, causing the victim’s value to be bridged into attacker-selected assets.","The same redirection works through the `*WithTransferPermit` variants because the signed transfer only covers moving funds into the bridge token, not the final bridge recipient or chain."],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-003","severity":"High","confidence":"medium","title":"Cross-chain trade entrypoints burn source funds immediately but provide no on-chain recovery path if destination execution reverts","locations":["onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:354","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:362","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:367","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:375","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:377","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:382","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:396","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:398","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:412","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:425","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:426","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:432","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:441","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:442","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:443","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:448","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:456","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:461","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:469","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:471","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:476","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:490","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:492","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:506","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:519","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:520","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:526","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:535","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:536","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:537","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:538","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:541"],"claim":"All outbound cross-chain trade entrypoints irreversibly burn the source-side bridge token as soon as the request is made, but the contract stores no pending order, escrow claim, or refund state. If the later destination-side execution reverts because the route is invalid, liquidity disappears, `amountOutMin` is unattainable, the native path is invalid, or the final native transfer fails, the inbound transaction simply reverts and there is no on-chain mechanism to restore the already-burned source funds.","impact":"Users can suffer permanent fund loss or long-lived lockup when the destination leg cannot be executed under the requested conditions. A failed cross-chain trade leaves value depending on off-chain operator intervention rather than any enforceable on-chain recovery path, creating realistic loss scenarios during market movement, liquidity withdrawal, destination-chain outages, or recipient-side transfer failures.","paths":["A user calls `anySwapOutExactTokensForTokens` or an underlying variant; the source token is burned immediately, but later `getAmountsOut`/pair resolution on the destination chain reverts because the path is invalid or liquidity no longer exists.","A user calls `anySwapOutExactTokensForNative`; the source burn succeeds, but destination execution reverts because the path no longer satisfies `amountOutMin`, the path does not end in `wNATIVE`, or the recipient cannot receive native coin.","After the source-side burn finalizes, adverse price movement on the destination chain makes the originally requested swap infeasible; because no refund state is recorded on-chain, the user has no protocol-level way to reclaim the burned source assets."],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-004","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"User trade deadlines are enforced only on the source chain and can be bypassed on destination execution","locations":["onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:182","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:183","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:207","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:208","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:354","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:359","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:363","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:432","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:438","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:440","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:448","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:453","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:457","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:526","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:532","onchain_auto/0x765277eebeca2e31912c9946eae1021199b39c61/Contract.sol:534"],"claim":"The swap-style outbound functions check `deadline` only when the source-chain burn request is submitted, but the bridge events do not record the deadline at all. On the destination chain, `anySwapInExactTokensForTokens` and `anySwapInExactTokensForNative` accept a fresh caller-supplied deadline and only validate that new value, allowing execution after the user’s original expiry.","impact":"Users cannot enforce their intended time limit across chains. A relayer or MPC can settle the trade long after the user expected it to expire, exposing the position to stale execution, market drift, and MEV that the deadline was meant to prevent.","paths":["A user submits a cross-chain swap with a short deadline to avoid stale fills; the source burn succeeds before expiry, but the operator later calls the destination `anySwapInExactTokensFor*` function with a new future deadline and the swap still executes.","During destination-chain congestion, the operator waits until market conditions favor them, then re-submits the inbound swap with a fresh deadline even though the user’s original deadline has already passed."],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]}],"rejected_candidates":[{"title":"Inbound bridge executions are replayable because processed tx hashes are never recorded","source_agents":["codex_1"],"reason":"`txs` is only emitted metadata; the trusted `onlyMPC` role can already call `anySwapIn*` with arbitrary parameters, so lack of on-chain replay tracking does not create a distinct, non-privileged exploit path."},{"title":"MPC 2-day delay bypassed on initial deployment","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"The constructor needs an immediately active MPC so the router is operable after deployment; the 2-day delay applies to later MPC changes, not initial bootstrap."},{"title":"Slippage protection parameter accepted but not enforced","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"`amountOutMin` is enforced on the destination-side `anySwapInExactTokensForTokens` and `anySwapInExactTokensForNative` calls. The real issue is missing on-chain commitment/recovery for cross-chain execution, which is captured separately."},{"title":"Batch function arrays not validated for equal length","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Mismatched array lengths only cause the caller’s own transaction to revert via bounds checks; this is not a realistic protocol-level loss, theft, insolvency, or permissionless DoS issue."},{"title":"Initial _oldMPC is address(0) causing undefined behavior during transitions","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"On the first `changeMPC`, `_oldMPC` is assigned `mpc()`, which returns the currently active `_newMPC`, not zero. The claimed zero-address transition window does not occur."},{"title":"Plain anySwapOut lacks minimum amount parameter","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"`anySwapOut` is a simple bridge burn/mint flow, not a swap execution path with price discovery, so an `amountOutMin` parameter is not relevant there."}]}
