o `TEAM_ADDRESS`."],"round":6,"source_agents":["codex"]}],"rejected_candidates":[{"title":"Silent Compound redeem failures can turn withdrawn principal into team-sweepable “interest”","source_agents":["codex"],"reason":"Merged into F-005 as a materially stronger exploit path for the existing ignored-Compound-return-codes finding rather than kept as a separate duplicate."},{"title":"The EOA-only referrer restriction is bypassable by contracts in construction","source_agents":["codex"],"reason":"The constructor-time `extcodesize` bypass is real, but this contract only stores referral metadata; no on-chain payout, privilege, or protocol-fund impact is implemented here."},{"title":"Referral registration can be claimed after prior staking activity by using unsupported tokens first","source_agents":["codex"],"reason":"This only weakens the intended referral-eligibility policy for metadata tracking; with no on-chain referral reward or privileged action wired up, realistic protocol-level harm is too speculative."}]}
